        <div class="msgSubject">Inventory Changes</div>
        <div class="sm notbold">
          
          Posted: 2010-11-20 13:47:34 | Edited: Nov 20 2010  3:41pm  | <input type="checkbox" name="quote-1290282454327433880" id="quote-1290282454327433880" class="msgQuoteCheck" onchange="multiQuote2()"/><label for="quote-1290282454327433880" onclick="multiQuote2()"> Quote</label>  | <a href="/forum.html?forum=173&amp;mid=1290282454327433880&amp;post=1&amp;replyto=1290282454327433880&amp;page=1" class="icon-replytothis" rel="nofollow">Reply to Post</a> | <a id="FOLLOW_MID_1290282454327433880" onclick="followToggle('add','1290282454327433880')" href="javascript:" class="icon-follow">Follow</a> 
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgWhoFrame">
        <div class="msgUM"><a class="msgWhoName Scholar" href="/users/kgav">kgav</a><div class="msgWhoTitle Scholar">Scholar</div></div><div class="msgAvatar"></div><div class="msgStar"><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/></div><div class="msgWhoNum">1,475 posts</div>
        <div class="msgScore">
          Score: Decent  
          <div class="msgRatings"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">Instead of thinking of materials in terms of stacks SE's 2nd generation MMO should think of a quantity of like crafting materials as residing in pouches. <br /> <br />So if a character's inventory is a backpack then groups of like crafting materials would be deposited into pouches within the backpack. In this way a single pouch could contain normal quality, +1, +2, and +3 variant of the same crafting material. If inventory is simply a directory with a set number of listings then any one of those listings could be a subdirectory. The subdirectory can have a listing for each available variant of a material. <br /> <br />The combined number of all quality variants of the same material could still be limited to a total, for example 99 total items. The 99 total could be 90 normal, 6 +1s and 3 +3s, or any combination of variants. When crafting a pouch is opened and the desired quality is chosen or the lowest quality variant can be instantly selected without entering a selection sub-menu. <br /> <br />This isn't even really a next generation feature, many other MMOs allow for bags being placed within bags. It is time SE stopped implementing features in such myopic ways. <br /> <br /> <br />Example - <span style="color:blue">Root level of inventory</span> <span style="color:gold">Contents of a Pouch</span> <span style="color:gray">Invisible in UI</span> <span style="color:green">UI Behaviors</span> <br /> <br /> <br />-Inventory <br /><span style="color:blue">--Cotton Boll 99</span> <span style="color:green">&lt;- This is all that is displayed at the root level of the inventory. Right-Click pops up content.</span> <br /><span style="color:gold">----Cotton Boll +0-90 <br />----Cotton Boll +1-06</span> <br /><span style="color:gray">----Cotton Boll +2-00</span> <br /><span style="color:gold">----Cotton Boll +3-03</span> <br /> <br /> <br />-Inventory <br /><span style="color:blue">--Cotton Boll +1 09</span> <span style="color:green">&lt;--Named for lowest quality variant with a quantity.  <br />------------------------------Left-Click selects named variant automatically.  <br />------------------------------Right-Click opens and allows selection of variant. <br />------------------------------Cursor-Hover-Over displays quantities of variants.</span> <br /><span style="color:gray">----Cotton Boll +0-00</span> <br /><span style="color:gold">----Cotton Boll +1-06</span> <span style="color:green">&lt;--+1 is the lowest and has 6 quantity so the pouch is named after it.</span>   <br /><span style="color:gold">----Cotton Boll +2-00 <br />----Cotton Boll +3-03</span> <br /> <br /><span style="color:green">A stack of a single quality variant has a normal icon, a stack with multiple quality variants has a gold border around the icon.</span> <br /> <br />I know SE has stated that they are going to remove/replace +1 &amp; +2 materials with +3 to eliminate the number of stacks but I believe that is a clumsy solution. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 20th 2010  4:41pm by kgav </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://www.enjin.com" rel="external nofollow" title="www.enjin.com">[img]<a href="http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/3529_48d6215903dff562.png" title="http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/3529_48d6215903dff562.png" rel="external nofollow">http://sigs.enjin.com/sig-ffxiv/3529_48d6215903dff562.png</a>[/img]</a> <br /><b>Rai</b> [Elvaan] [Rank 10] [Leviathan] <br />75PLD | 50RNG| 75NIN | 56WAR | 37RDM | 44BLU | 45BST | 37THF | 26WHM | 40BLM | 20BRD | 11COR | 22MNK | 37DRK | 75DRG | 37SAM | 18SMN | 8PUP <br /></div></div>
